text: Turner is an unincorporated community in Columbia County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== Turner was platted in 1902 by B. M. Turner, and named for him. A post office called Turner was established in 1904, and remained in operation until 1934. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Columbia County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Turner, Washington
